post_text:
As we work to provide school age child care for a school year like no other, the number of staff needed has increased. If you know of anyone who loves kids, is responsible, is age 18 or older and would be interested and available to work in our child care programs, please ask them to review our job openings list on the district website and apply: http://bit.ly/192ChildCareHiringNow

We start on Monday and we'd love to fill our open positions as soon as possible. We also have a number of paraprofessional positions available. If you know of someone who would be interested in the the positions but can’t commit to a regular schedule, we are in need of substitute staff as well. They may call (651) 463-5040 or (651) 460-3200 or the Community Education office for more information on subbing.

Thank you for your support!

Farmington Area Community Education

Farmington High School Band
May 25 at 7:54 AM ·

We're very proud to be a part of Farmington's annual Memorial Day program. This year, in place of our traditional performance at Corinthian Cemetery, we are extremely proud to have FHS Band students taking part in "Taps Across America" at 3pm.

Thousands of trumpet & bugle players across the nation will step outside their homes today at 1500 local time to perform, but we've gone one step further and invited ANYONE in our band program to be a part of it.

Please pause today at 3 and listen for Taps in your neighborhood. We are proud to take part in this meaningful program in honor of all fallen heroes.

[ Pictured: Griffin Neu, FHS Class of 2017, performing Taps at Corinthian Cemetery. Photo courtesy of Lynne Halterman Images ]

#WeAre192 | #FarmingtonMN | #MemorialDay | #CBSTaps

Farmington Area Public Schools | Farmington Area Veterans Memorial | City of Farmington, MN - Local Government | Farmington VFW Sypal Lundgren Post #7662 | Farmington Police Department - Minnesota | FHS Tigers Activities | Farmington Tiger Band Booster

Farmington Area Public Schools, ISD 192 has held a district-wide art show since 1992. Although we are unable to hold the show in person this year, our art teachers were determined to bring the show to our community virtually. To that end, they photographed all the art pieces that would have been shared at the show and have compiled them here for you to see.

The 2020 District Art Show represents all schools and about 500 pieces of student artwork. Looking for a close up of a specific piece? Families can see their student's artwork up-close or even download pictures here:

Middle School Art - https://www.smore.com/tsnyg

post_text: Check out what our FHS band students have been up to during this time of distance learning. We are so inspired by our amazing Tigers and we hope you are too! 🧡
shared_text:
Farmington High School Band
April 30 at 10:00 AM ·

We need this more than ever. Our STUDENTS needed this more than ever. Here is a project that gives us hope!

We challenged every one of our band members to use their passions, interests, and talents to create something new and beautiful and expressive, inspired by our band music. We received everything from digital art and animation to research papers, poetry, and Lego sculptures! They built rockets; wrote passionate reflections; and submitted paintings, drawings, watercolors, and so much more.

Please take a couple minutes to let this video brighten your day. Leave some love for these students who reveal so much about themselves and how they're keeping busy during Distance Learning.

Today we're featuring Nathan Yager, Farmington High School Counselor, for #TeacherTuesday!

Mr. Yager is new to Farmington High School but has served in education since 2015. Before becoming an educator he worked in sales, business management, and heavy equipment operations but he said, "None of my previous occupations gave me a sense of accomplishment like being an educator has."

Mr. Yager describes himself as someone who is "family focused" and loves being outside.

"I hope that our students use their skills and talents in service to each other."

Thank you for the great work you're doing, Mr. Yager, and welcome to our Tiger community! #WeAre192

post_text:
Today we would like to say a big thank you to Julie Mogensen, a special education teacher at Farmington Elementary!

Ms. Mogensen has been teaching special education for 23 years. Outside of school she enjoys spending time with family and friends, usually at a football, basketball or softball game. Her favorite book is Freckle Juice by Judy Blume ("I love having the kids make the secret recipe and then tasting it to see if they end up getting freckles," she said.). Her favorite food is anything she doesn't have to cook.

In her own words, "My hope for my students is that they find what they are passionate about and use that passion to set the world on fire."

#TeacherTuesday | #WeAre192

Today we're featuring Jan Lokhorst, a Language Arts teacher at Dodge Middle School. This is Ms. Lokhorst's 40th year teaching and her 35th year in Farmington Area Public Schools!

Outside of school she enjoys reading, going for walks, and following the Twins and the Vikings. Her favorite season is fall because she loves the beautiful, colorful leaves.

In her own words: "I really like teaching sixth grade because everyday brings something new and interesting from the students. I hope my students have a love for learning and continue to learn as they venture through life."

Thank you, Ms. Lokhorst! #TeacherTuesday #WeAre192

post_text:
It's #TeacherTuesday! Today we are featuring Kevin Waldbillig, an eighth grade math teacher at Boeckman Middle School.

Mr. Waldbillig has been teaching middle school math in Farmington for 33 years. Outside of teaching he loves good barbecue ribs, ice cream, gardening, and spending time with his family. He's also a huge fan of the Minnesota Twins.

In his own words:
"I love watching students' faces light up or seeing them smile when they have been struggling to understand a topic and they finally have success at it. It is the best feeling knowing that you were, in some small way, a part of that growth process for them. It's awesome to see the growth in understanding of math content and strategies from the students over the school year."

Thank you Mr. Waldbillig, for all you do! #WeAre192

It's #TeacherTuesday! This year we want to feature more of our awesome teachers and the important work they're doing.

For the first #TeacherTuesday of the school year, meet Julie Heckmann! Ms. Heckmann teaches first grade at Akin Road Elementary.

In her own words: "I believe that building relationships with each student is vital to their success in and out of the classroom. Every student comes with a set of gifts that make them special. I can’t wait to see what the future holds for our students.
"One fun fact about myself is that I played guitar in a folk band in high school that traveled to Germany and throughout the Midwest."

Thank you Ms. Heckmann, for all you do! #WeAre192

In the world of college admission, May 1st represents #NationalDecisionDay, the day by which colleges and universities typically require students to accept or reject an offer of admission. To help the class of 2019 celebrate their next steps, the FHS Counseling Department and Administration invited all seniors to the Commons for graduation cake and pictures. Every senior and all choices (community and technical college, 4 year colleges and universities, military, and entering the workforce) are celebrated at FHS. Congratulations class of 2019!

Photo Credit: Farmington Girls' Swim & Dive

post_text: Congratulations to these All State musicians from #ISD192!
shared_text:
Farmington High School Choir
May 1, 2019 at 10:13 AM ·

It is with immense pride that we announce our selections to the 2019-2020 All-State Choir and Band program. 🎶This year we had 13 honorees, a record for both our choir and band programs. We are so proud of these students for their hard work and dedication - the All-State Music program is truly the highest honor for a high school music student and it is a very competitive audition process. 🎶

Please join us in congratulating these choir members and the members of the Farmington High School Band.

Choir Members include Isaac Bui (TTBB Choir), Lucas Laden (TTBB Choir), Eric Markwardt (TTBB Choir), Jack Baumbach (TTBB Choir), Alex Kiage (SATB Choir), and Teresa Kiminski (SSAA Choir).

Band Members include Charlie Kiel (euphonium), Caelan Hubred (Jazz Band trombone), Ryland Cook (Jazz Band trombone), Lucas Dentinger (percussion), Emily Berghuis (clarinet), Logan Watters (trumpet), and Jace Sterner (trombone alternate).

BRAVI TUTTI!

Farmington Area Public Schools Farmington Independent Tiger Fan Club Minnesota Music Educators Association

Attention ALL high school students and families in Farmington and surrounding communities: The College Fair is coming to FHS! More than 100 public and private colleges and universities, community and technical colleges, and military organizations will be represented at Farmington High School on Thursday, March 21st, from 4 p.m. to 5:30 p.m. in the commons.

This is an important opportunity for students and families to explore post-secondary options. The College Fair is FREE and open to ALL students and families in Farmington and surrounding communities.

Prior to attending the college fair students need to register at www.gotocollegefairs.com.

Don't forget to share your back-to-school story with us on social media using #192Back2School.

For the latest news and fun stories from all our schools and programs, follow Farmington Area Public Schools on Facebook, Twitter, and Instagram @District192 | #ISD192 | #192TigerPride.

post_text:
Happy last day of school to all our #ISD192 secondary students! Best of luck on your final finals of the year! =) To our seniors, we'll see you tomorrow for graduation. To everyone else, we'll look forward to seeing you in the fall.

Keep in touch and let us know how your summer is going, and we'll tell you about ours too, using the hashtag #192Summer!
